What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

the features of interest are the prosper rating and its relatioship with other factors. Also the loan status and the ability to predict which may be completed and which may be defaulted.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I think the borrow rate and the prosperrating will be depending on the income and the employments status, and that would support the investigation. Also the loan amount should make a huge impact on the result.

In [38]:
def cat_bar_plot(df, column, gen_order): # defining a function that plots a bar for a categorical univariate

    base_color= sb.color_palette()[0] # choosing the color
    plt.xticks(rotation= 90) # rotating the xticks so they can be readable
    sb.countplot(data=df, x= column, color=base_color, order=gen_order); # plotting the bars
    plt.title(column)

In [53]:
# rechaping the loan categories to keep the highest categories and add the rest to the 'other'
categories_dict = {1: 'Debt Consolidation', 2: 'Home Improvement', 3: 'Business', 6: 'Auto', 7: 'Other'}

def categorize(df):
    loan_category = df['ListingCategory (numeric)']
    if  loan_category in categories_dict:
        return categories_dict[loan_category]
    else:
        return categories_dict[7]
    
project_df['ListingCategory (numeric)'] = project_df.apply(categorize, axis=1)
project_df['ListingCategory (numeric)'].value_counts()

Conclusions¶

  • The majority of borrowers are employed and the highest count of prosper rating is 'A'
  • The most frequent rating for the defaulted loans is E and The most frequent rating in the completed loans is AA
  • The highest number of loans are from the Debt Consolidation and least in from the Auto.
  • It looks like the defaulted loans are larger in the amount than the completed loans
  • The highest income is directly related to prosper rating AA and the lowest is HR then E
  • AA rating seems to have higher defaulted loans even thogh they have the highest income
